metadata.name: A Sneak Peak
metadata.description:
As I drove up the I-70 that day I knew I had one goal in mind, today I was to capture my first Peak! I didn't remember exactly where I saw it before, or even what the view was like, but I remembered passing the valley earlier that week in my travels around Colorado. Suddenly, it snuck up on me and all I got was a quick tease of the view as I flew by on the freeway. I wondered if this was even the spot I was looking for and kept driving for another few miles to check the views farther up. They didn't even compare! As I turned the car around I could feel my pulse starting to pick up.  It was finally time for my coming of age as a landscape photographer. 

It was time for A Sneak Peak.

A Sneak Peak tells a tale of when two seasons collide.  The delicate balance between the two in the mountains of Colorado is like the blooming of springs first flowers. You can watch the progress of Winter sneaking in and wake up one morning still surprised by the fast progress the seasons make.

I fell in love with the mountains of Colorado and I hope "A Sneak Peak" helps you to see them through my perspective.


Title: A Sneak Peak  
Artist: TheShutterPrince  
Editions: 1/1
